  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Lazarus</title>

    <para>
      Ensure that the source tree is in proper state:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc clean</userinput></screen>

<!--
  Looks like that even both versions (gtk2, qt5) can be on one machine
  when the binaries 'lazarus' and 'startlazarus' are moved to
    lazarus      -> lazarus-gtk2
    startlazarus -> startlazarus-gtk2
  and after building the QT5 variant
    lazarus      -> lazarus-qt5
    startlazarus -> startlazarus-qt5
  and than symlink lazarus/startlazarus to the desired ones.
  (it needs to be analyzed more deeply)

  Instructions are taken from ArchLinux and adopted to LFS
-->
    <para>
      If you want to build <application>Lazarus</application> with
      the gtk2 toolkit, build the package by running the following
      commands, otherwise proceed to build the QT5 based variant below.
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc LCL_PLATFORM=gtk2 bigide</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you have built the gtk2 variant, skip the QT5 section and
      proceed to the installation. Otherwise 
      <application>Lazarus</application> is built using the
      QT5 library by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make -j1 FPC=/usr/bin/fpc LCL_PLATFORM=qt5 bigide</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This package does not come with a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, install <application>lazarus</application> as the
      <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr distinstall

mv /usr/share/lazarus/docs /usr/share/doc/lazarus

mv /usr/share/lazarus /usr/lib/
for L in $(find /usr/bin -type l); do
    ln -svf "$(readlink $L | sed 's@/share/@/lib/@')" "$L"
done

sed -e 's|\(Categories\).*|\1=IDE;Development;|' \
    -i /usr/share/applications/lazarus.desktop

install -Dm644 images/ide_icon48x48.png \
       /usr/share/pixmaps/lazarus.png</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

